 A former lawmaker representing Kaduna Central Senatorial District at the National Assembly, Shehu Sani, has arrived the Federal High Court, Abuja, ahead of the commencement of trial of rights activist and journalist, Omoyele Sowore. Sani joins Nobel laureate, Prof Wole Soyinka, and other important personalities that turned up at the court to support Sowore, who is facing charges of cyberstalking and treason brought against him by the Nigerian Government. LIVE BLOG: @ShehuSani arrives in court in support of Sowore. #SoworevsFG #FreeSoworeNOWFOLLOW LIVE: https://t.co/ySdyLdrcRh pic.twitter.com/qIWJIvcwyI 